			<h1>Discovering Constraints and Prioritizing Opportunities</h1>
			<h2>Research, Strategy</h2>
			<p class="text">
			Although the product owners asked for a responsive update, after several talks with engineering, it was clear that a more gradual approach was necessary. As a result, we had to prioritize the updates&#8212;a necessary step in almost all projects.
			</br></br>
			My favorite prioritization tool is user research&#8212;even if only a small amount, a few insights goes a long way. 
			</br></br>
			I created a short <em>research plan</em> to gain better insight into how users access the product and how they might use a more fluid web experience. The research was quick and lean but the findings were inspiring.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="outputs">
		<div class="content-grid">
		<h4>An <em>Interview Script</em> I made was given to the research department to guide a series of user interviews and user tests.</h4>
			<div class="outputs-gallery">
				 <a href="images/nfl-script.png" rel="gallery-research" class="gallery">
