			<h1>Prototyping a Solution</h1>
			<h2>Prototyping, User Testing</h2>
			<p class="text">The final iteration did not focus on making parts of the app responsive but focused on what users cared about the most: watching the game while doing other things. </br></br>
			To test and communicate a more refined concept, we raised the fidelity up a notch. Working with another designer who created high-fidelity assets, I <em>prototyped</em> the interactions and user flow using HTML, CSS, and little bit of JS magic. This helped communicate the desired behavior to both the engineers and product owners and gave us something to put in front of the users.</p>
			</br>
			<span class="caption">The feature was called "stadium mode" and it let the users view just the live video module in a scalable browser. Click the image below to watch a video of a preliminary prototype.</span> 
